# MUI Color/Palette Rules

## 1. No Tailwind or manually written CSS classes for colors
- Only use palette keys provided by the MUI theme: primary, secondary, error, warning, info, success, background, text.
- For all custom colors: extend theme.palette.

## 2. Example Usage
```typescript
<Box sx={{ bgcolor: 'background.paper', color: 'text.primary', p: 2 }}>Content</Box>
<Button color="primary">Save</Button>
<Button color="error">Delete</Button>
```

## 3. Defining Custom Brand Colors
```typescript
const theme = createTheme({
  palette: {
    primary: { main: '#e85a4f' },
    brand: { main: '#aabbcc' } // custom slot if needed
  }
});
```

## 4. Never use CSS variables or Tailwind mapping in component code.